11:46 <@jhf:#liferay> you can assign a mobile theme to be used when a particular device (or set of device families) is detected.
11:46 < webczat:#liferay> actually I'd be happy to disable responsiveness
11:46 <@jhf:#liferay> but the 'classic' theme as shipped with liferay doesn't do that - instead it uses special CSS classes to 'respond' to the size of the screen on which it is rendered.
